  "text": "For soybean, when the first trifoliate of the soybean seedling opened, the nutrient solution was replaced by the fresh 1/2 Hoagland's solution containing 0.9% NaCl (w/v) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . To extract the total RNA, the leaves and roots were collected and ground in liquid nitrogen separately at 0 h, 4 h, 24 h, 48 h, and 72 h after the start of salt treatments [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . For Arabidopsis, three-week-old seedlings grown in the hydroponic system were transferred to the fresh 1/10 MS solution supplemented with 100 mM NaCl. The sampling time points were 0 h, 1 h, 3 h, 6 h, 12 h, and 24 h after the start of salt treatments. Three individual plants under the same treatment were pooled into one biological sample.",
